<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-687-710  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 687 710.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computers in Banking  Sept 1989 v6 n9 p26(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>NCNB exploits its systems integration skills for growth. (NorthCarolina National Bank) (company profile)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Tracey, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The North Carolina National Bank (NCNB) increases its influence byacquiring banks in Florida and, most recently, Texas.andP;  Theirtechnique is to combine, then conquer; operations in Florida wereconsolidated into one data center and NCNB plans to make a singleconsolidated statewide bank out of Texas' First Republic bankchain (formerly RepublicBank and Interfirst Bank).andP;  NCNB runstheir banks on IBM's top-of-the-line mainframes and uses MVSseries operating systems.andP;  Select areas of reorganization arebranch automation via the Consumer Loan Application and ScoringSystem (CLASS), cash management services, and the special assetsdivision (SAD) which is a &quot;bad bank&quot; for loans where losses arecovered by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corp (FDIC) afterrefinance or foreclosure has failed.andP;  NCNB is attempting to createa distinctly defined, chain-of-command organization whilecontinuing to look into new technologies like electronic datainterchange and computer-aided software engineering.andP;  Expansion isthe goal and their system capabilities are primed for it.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   North Carolina National Bank (growth).andO;Topic:     CompetitionAcquisitionBankingManagementIntegrated SystemsCompany Profile.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>